edu.uidaho.junicon.interpreter.interpreter

Interface IScriptEval

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ISubstrate
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSubstrate

    public interface IScriptEval
    Evaluates scripts and sets bindings for the environment. Scripts are typically evaluated using a given ScriptEngine specified by its script extension, e.g., "js".

        String invokeMethod(String objectName,
                    String methodName,
                    String[] args)
             throws ScriptException
        Invokes object method in the given script engine. See: javax.script.Invocable.
        Parameters:

        methodName - method name
        args - parameters
        Returns:
        result of method call, or null if not String
        Throws:
        ScriptException - if script error occurs, if object or method not found, or if ScriptEngine is not Invocable.
